content.description: Sit down start with the upside down V crack. Move right to a curved edge, throw to the lip and top out above.Beta Video

Same start as First to Find - SDS with low left side pull and right sloper. Move up and right to the long juggy crack. Traverse the crack and top out to the right. Positive holds and tricky feet make for some great climbing.Beta Video
content.location:
On the side of the boulder facing the parking lot. 

 GPS: 40.04919, -75.03737

content.description: Start low on an upside down V shaped crack and move up and left along jugs on the overhang. Top out directly above the overhang.Beta Video
content.location: Start is on the backside of the boulder.

content.description: Standstart matched on the large side pull. Use the large crimp to step up onto the left slab and move up.Beta VideoVariation V0: Same SDS as First to Start but set left onto the slab using the crimp.
content.location:
On the side of the boulder facing the parking lot.

 GPS: 40.04919, -75.03737

content.description: Start low on the upside down V shaped crack and move up and left along jugs on the overhanging. Make a wide move to the jug left of the overhang. Move up and left to the top with tricky feet. The top of the overhang is off.Beta Video
content.location: The start is on the back of the boulder.

content.description: SDS with the lowest part of the large side pull and a slopey feature to the right on the bulge. Bump your right to a jug and move up on crimps at the top.Beta Video
content.location:
The side of the boulder that faces the parking lot.

 GPS: 40.04919, -75.03737

content.description:
Sit down start with the upside down V crack. Traverse right to the long sloping shelf. Continue along the shelf until you reach the large vertical sidepull. Mantle up onto the shelf or top put with a hold high on the large sidepull.

Beta Video
Stand start on the left end of the long juggy crack. Traverse right and move up to top out.
content.location: Just right of First To Find.

content.description: This is one sweet little rock. Lots of slopers and interesting shapes, almost like diabase. There are several routes from V-easy to V3 with excellent landings. A great spot to warm up before heading down to Deer Rock. Found this spot on geocaching.com.
